 Thandeka Moyo A Nyamandlovu man was found dead on Wednesday morning outside the Apostolic Faith Mission Church  (AFM) in Bulawayo’s high density suburb of Pelandaba. The lifeless body of the man, believed to be an AFM congregant,  was spotted by passerby’s at around 6Am, a few metres from the church along along Khami Road. It is believed that the said the man was rushing to meet up with fellow congregants when he fell and died on the road. More details to follow…